The paper deals with the complexity of counting homomorphisms, surjective homomorphisms, and compactions, which are all topics related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves graph theory, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The complexity analysis of these problems involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are topics covered in computer science theory (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
